of the Vegas hotel deals with Bookit threw in a Cirque du Soleil ticket. We thought that was a pretty decent perk.","Bookit offers some, but not all, of the filters we looked for. Once you type in your vacation dates this site will narrow down your choice of hotel deals according to their price, guest rating, hotel name, star rating and list of amenities.","We were able to put in some dates for Las Vegas and have Bookit.com narrow our list down to only pet-friendly hotels with an outdoor pool with four or more star ratings and four or more guest ratings that were on the Las Vegas Strip. That’s pretty good for filters but other hotel booking sites have even more, including sliding filters for things like price range and easy ways to find hotel deals near specific landmarks. Other hotel booking sites also offer much more information about each hotel’s area of town.","We also would have liked to find more accessibility filters on Bookit.com. Seems like it would be a pretty easy thing to research, and when you are in need of wheelchair access rooms at your hotel there is really no substitute. We also would prefer an easy way to narrow by hotel type, whether large resort, bed and breakfast or something in between. This was a valuable tool we found on other hotel booking sites.","This site was not the best in terms of organization. The advertisements are a part of the layout on many pages. We realize Bookit.com has to make money like any business but some of the ads are formatted to look just like hotel listings. It gets really annoying for the consumer.","Bookit’s descriptions of each hotel are extensive and we like all the detail they include. Amenities are summarized into a quick-reference bullet list at the bottom of the page, or you can read the summary for more specific information. We were not keen on the small, grayish text, but most people will refer more to the bulleted amenities lists than the full descriptions anyway.","We loved the links to YouTube videos for some of the hotels on Bookit. These really go beyond the virtual tours offered on most hotel booking sites. We wish all hotel booking sites would include videos like this. Slide shows with totally staged photos do not paint the kind of accurate picture that videos can. No doubt the videos are taken on the days when the hotel is at its cleanest and best, and the visitors interviewed are of course the ones that went away happy so you don’t know that will be your exact experience, but actually seeing the hotel in video format is priceless. The videos were not available for every hotel on Bookit, though. What a tremendous resource they were for the customer though.","The video tours/reviews almost make up for the small number of written guest ratings, something we would like to see more of on Bookit. These first-hand accounts are an invaluable resource if you are traveling somewhere new. In every single case we were surprised by how few guest reviews were posted on this site. The ones Bookit had were easy to find and helpful. We just wish there were more of them.","The maps for each hotel were helpful and easy to find. We liked the inclusion of the distance to popular sites just below the map. We also found directions to and from the nearest airport on most of the Bookit hotel pages we looked at. That was very useful information.","We weren’t able to easily find information on nearby eateries aside from restaurants inside each hotel. More on that topic would have been helpful.","Customer support is pretty decent. You can contact them by phone, email or mail. Their phone hours are fairly limited, though, so a live chat feature would be a great addition. Their phone lines are open Monday through Friday from 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. and on Saturday and Sunday from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Eastern Standard Time. We found the hold times to be pretty long when we did our test calls. We made it to 10 minutes on one call and five on another before giving up and hanging up. That hold time could be a bad thing if you are standing in a hotel lobby with a question about your booking, though most problems will have to be resolved with the hotel anyway."]},"id":"07115b31-c3a5-4c67-ad19-d18fa11fdd73","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"fcafef5e-f1d9-40f2-92e7-7e502bc1c065","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Bookit may not be best if you have a specific trip you&#39;re planning for, but if you have some time off and can go wherever the best hotel deals will take you, this site can help. Whenever we tested it against other sites for hotel deals on specific dates this site fell short, but we saw some pretty good random hotel deals every time we checked Bookit. We also liked the video reviews for some of the Bookit hotels. However, Bookit could use more filters for helping customers narrow down their searches and would benefit from more user ratings."]},"id":"d7140b9d-2817-42f0-bbc8-2bbebe75a341","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_53107","url":"/bookit-com-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"eli-mccormick","url":"/author/eli-mccormick","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Eli McCormick","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"CSoTtbWogSTgZ9Xgr3Anr9","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2011-06-24T20:12:04Z","datePublished":"2011-06-24T20:12:04Z","name":"BookIt.com","synopsis":"Editor's Note: This review has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it no longer ranks in our lineup. The original review is below, but check out our current top products about Hotel Booking Services here. One of the Bookit.com core values is “guest elation.\"","review":{"rating":74,"verdict":"Bookit has good deals at times but lacks some of the good organization we saw on other sites. ","pros":["The excellent hotel descriptions on this site are very detailed and include video tours."],"cons":["A few more filters would be helpful."]},"strapline":"Editor